    },
    {
      "name": "daysSinceEpoch",
      "dataType": "INT",
      â€œtransformFunctionâ€: â€œGroovy({timestamp/(1000*60*60*24)}, timestamp)â€
    }
  ],
   "timeFieldSpec": {
    "incomingGranularitySpec": {
      "name": "hoursSinceEpoch",
      "dataType": "LONG",
      "timeFormat" : "EPOCH",
      "timeType": "HOURS",
      â€œtransformFunctionâ€: â€œGroovy({timestamp/(1000*60*60)}, timestamp)â€
    }
  }
}
```
we would want to add a new top-level element in that json with a transformFunction  like
```
{
  "schemaName": "events",
  "filter": "Groovy({cost > 42}, cost)",
  "dimensionFieldSpecs": [
    {
      "name": "userId",
      "dataType": "LONG",
      â€œtransformFunctionâ€: â€œGroovy({userID}, userID)â€
    },
    ...
  ],
  ...
}
```
Then we would apply a row-based filter based on that transformFunction either
a) On source columns - applying the rest of the transformations AFTER filtering
or
b) On transformed columns - applying the filtering after the rest of the transformations.

Is that all right? Am I on the right track?

